# Linux Server Hardening Automation with Ansible

## Project Overview

This project focuses on the automation of Linux server hardening using Ansible in order to improve system security within an institutional environment. The objective is to implement security best practices and automate configuration processes to reduce vulnerabilities and improve the management of Linux servers.

The project was developed as part of the **Cybersecurity Professional Internship Program**, applying automation techniques and risk analysis methodologies to strengthen the security posture of server infrastructures.

---

## Project Objectives

- Automate Linux server hardening using Ansible.
- Reduce security vulnerabilities caused by misconfigurations.
- Implement security policies and best practices.
- Develop a cybersecurity risk matrix for server environments.
- Improve system administration efficiency through automation.

---

## Technologies Used

- **Linux**
- **Ansible**
- **YAML**
- **Cybersecurity Risk Analysis**
- **System Hardening Techniques**

